column5: enjoy your summer lew you will love your new ride

Enjoy Lew!! I hope the weather is nice and warm. We'll be at our trailer in HH every weekend and I plan on at least one day trip to musky fish in the Kawartha's, I'll let you know when so I can get to see the new ride up close and personal.

Ya...I was wunderin" how the grass was going to get taken care of also...  Have fun Lew and Diane...If you find yourself up this way terrorizing Meely's muskies watch out for the "Tin of Beans" on Tait's Bay...
Enjoy the summer bud!! See you next week!
Lew.. you left so fast.. did you remember to lock the door!
Well I look forward to seeing you in June ... Lew...  We'll have to try to get out together for a couple of hours... see if we can spook a big one!..       Best Regards,  the cap't

Well, it's finally that beautiful time of year again, the van is packed and me & the Mrs are outta here tomorrow morning at 8 A.M. for our little hide-away in the Kawarthas and we won't be back home again till mid-October  Nuthin for the 2 of us to do for the next 5 1/2 months but enjoy my new boat, plenty of musky fish'n, or just lay around under the shade trees and enjoy life.  I'm going to Lakair for 7 days in June for the g2g and I'll see a bunch of you there,  then a few of us have another 7 day Nippissing trip booked at a different location in August. There'll also be a couple more musky trips to both the Ottawa & St. Lawrence Rivers and where ever else the roads lead me.  I'll probably have to come back to the Smoke a couple times taking care of business, but they'll just be quick trips and I'll head back north as fast as possible.  I seldom take fish pictures anymore, but I always have my camera just incase.  So have a great summer everyone and stay safe on the water and I'll see y'all in the fall
No posts or nutin?  Gonna miss that. Have fun and enjoy, staying safe of course.  Good luck!
well, enjoy the boat and have a great time

Hey Lew, even if you don't get fish porn shots, at least send some scenery shots for those of us stuck in the city. Have a great summer. Mebbe I'll be lucky enuf to run into you if I get up there to visit Garry again.  JF

You two enjoy the highlife Lew!! You worked for it.. now get out there and live it!  We're in a holding pattern here... hope to at least make the lake for may 24.. but uncertain at this point. You've got my cell number if you're in the neighbourhood....
Good luck with the new boat and enjoy your spring and summer. If you see a kayak fisherman in Pigeon lake, come over and say Hi.
Enjoy Lew, enjoy. I'll see you in June my friend.
See You at Tim Hortons' Lew!!
Have a great one Lew. Hope you all have a wondeful summer. Enjoy the boat and we will see you in June..
Have fun Lew, hope to see you in June...  Maureen
Enjoy the new boat and have a great summer!
safe travels  see you tuesday night.  TB
See ya in June Lew ... hope you all have a great summer.
All the best to you and the Mrs on your get away. Take good care of yourself Lew your not as young as you use to be
Good travels! I am sooooo green with envy!
Sounds like you're living the life, Lew. All the best! Jim
man i can't wait til i retire so i can just fish   brb fast forwarding 40 years
Have a great summer bud.Sorry I am gonna miss you a Lakair in June but you never know..maybe a fall trip to the near nort' may happen.Take care and be safe... Joe

Good for you Lew. Hope to see you (and the new boat!) in June. I've got your number so hopefully we'll be able to get together at some point. May all your fish be slimy (unless its an incidental 8 lb bass...they are ok too)
What????? no trips home to cut the grass and give us a quick report on your adventures? Summer just won't be the same!  Take care Lew and enjoy!
Have a good summer and play safe.  C U in the fall for Quinte Mama's.  David  aka  Superdad
Enjoy your home away from home Lew, and your new boat.  See you in June.  Time for a rematch I think     Your turn to catch the biggest paddle  Joey
Have a great summer Lew. Enjoy that new boat and soak up all the joy you can.

You and Diane have the greatest summer, Lew. Hope to see you in June.  I still can't get over how selfless you are after buying that beautiful boat as a retirement present for Diane!  Be well my friend.

You and the Mrs have a great summer, Lew.  Enjoy the new ride.  You know where I'll be the last 2 weeks of June, first week of July and the last 2 weeks of August and the first 2 of Sept ... drop over if you have a chance.
